# Cursor Rules — AI Task Board (Frontend)
# Stack: React · TypeScript · Supabase · Tailwind CSS

---

## 1. PROJECT OVERVIEW

AI-powered task board (Trello-like) with:
- Kanban board UI
- AI task decomposition and assignment
- Telegram bot integration for task creation
- In-app AI chat assistant
- Subscription/payment flow

---

## 2. FOLDER STRUCTURE

```
src/
  components/       # Reusable UI components only (no business logic)
    board/          # Board, Column, Card, DragHandle
    ai/             # AiChat, AiTaskBreakdown, AiSuggestion
    payment/        # PricingModal, SubscriptionBanner
    telegram/       # TelegramConnect, TelegramStatus
    ui/             # Button, Input, Modal, Badge, Avatar (primitives)
  features/         # Feature slices (components + hooks + types co-located)
    board/
    ai/
    telegram/
    payment/
    auth/
  hooks/            # Shared custom hooks (useBoard, useAI, useUser)
  lib/
    supabase.ts     # Single Supabase client instance
    anthropic.ts    # Claude API wrapper
    utils.ts
  types/            # Global TypeScript types and DB schema types
  pages/            # Route-level components only
  store/            # Zustand slices (board, ui, user)
```

---

## 3. TYPESCRIPT

- Strict mode always on (`"strict": true`).
- No `any`. Use `unknown` and narrow with guards if needed.
- All Supabase table types must be generated from DB schema and imported from `src/types/supabase.ts`.
- Props interfaces named `[ComponentName]Props`.
- Event handlers typed explicitly: `React.MouseEvent<HTMLButtonElement>`, not just `MouseEvent`.
- Always type async function return values: `Promise<Task[]>`, not `Promise<any>`.

```ts
// ✅
async function fetchTasks(boardId: string): Promise<Task[]> { ... }

// ❌
async function fetchTasks(boardId) { ... }
```

---

## 4. SUPABASE

- One Supabase client. Never instantiate it outside `src/lib/supabase.ts`.
- All DB calls go through custom hooks (`useBoard`, `useTasks`, etc.) — never call `supabase` directly in components.
- Use Row Level Security (RLS) on every table. Never bypass RLS on the frontend.
- Realtime: use `supabase.channel()` for board updates (card move, new card, user assignment). Clean up channels in `useEffect` cleanup.
- Auth: use `supabase.auth` only. Session stored in Supabase — don't duplicate in localStorage.
- Handle all Supabase errors explicitly. Never ignore `error` from `{ data, error }`.

```ts
// ✅
const { data, error } = await supabase.from('tasks').select('*');
if (error) throw new Error(error.message);

// ❌
const { data } = await supabase.from('tasks').select('*');
```

---

## 5. COMPONENT RULES

- One component per file.
- Functional components only. No class components.
- Keep components under ~150 lines. Extract if larger.
- No business logic in UI components — use hooks.
- Derive UI state from data, not parallel state flags (`isLoading`, `isEmpty`, `isError` via `status` enum, not 3 booleans).
- Use `React.memo` only when profiling shows a real render problem.

```ts
// ✅ Status enum pattern
type Status = 'idle' | 'loading' | 'success' | 'error';

// ❌ Three parallel booleans
const [isLoading, setIsLoading] = useState(false);
const [isError, setIsError] = useState(false);
const [isSuccess, setIsSuccess] = useState(false);
```

---

## 6. AI TASK BREAKDOWN

- All Claude API calls go through `src/lib/anthropic.ts` — never call the API directly from components.
- Show streaming output in real time using `ReadableStream`. Display partial task list as it arrives.
- AI breakdown result must be validated before inserting into Supabase (check required fields: title, assigneeId, columnId).
- User must confirm AI-generated tasks before they are saved. Never auto-save AI output.
- Prompt templates live in `src/lib/prompts.ts` — not hardcoded in hooks.

```ts
// src/lib/prompts.ts
export const TASK_BREAKDOWN_PROMPT = (goal: string, users: User[]) => `...`;
```

---

## 7. AI CHAT (IN-APP)

- Chat state (messages history) lives in Zustand, not component state — persists across navigation.
- Send full conversation history to Claude on each turn.
- Render markdown responses with a lightweight parser (e.g., `react-markdown`).
- Max visible messages in UI: 100. Older messages collapsed, not removed from state.
- Chat has access to the current board context (board ID, column names, task count). Inject as system prompt context.

---

## 8. TELEGRAM INTEGRATION

- Telegram connection status shown in UI with clear states: `disconnected | pending | connected | error`.
- Users connect via a `/start` deeplink — generate and display the link, never ask for bot token from users.
- Tasks created via Telegram appear on the board via Supabase Realtime — no polling.
- Show Telegram origin badge on cards created through Telegram.

---

## 9. PAYMENT

- Payment UI is gated — show pricing modal when user hits a free plan limit, not before.
- Never store card data. Use Stripe Elements or hosted checkout only.
- Subscription status comes from Supabase (synced from webhook) — fetch on auth, cache in Zustand.
- Show clear plan limits in UI: "3/5 boards used", "Upgrade to add more members".
- Downgrade flow: warn before losing access, never silently delete data.

---

## 10. STATE MANAGEMENT (ZUSTAND)

- One Zustand store per feature slice: `useBoardStore`, `useUIStore`, `useUserStore`.
- Store only serializable data. No functions, no DOM refs.
- Server state (Supabase data) goes in React Query / hooks, not Zustand. Zustand is for UI state only.
- Persist only user preferences to localStorage (theme, collapsed columns). Never persist auth or tasks.

---

## 11. DRAG AND DROP

- Use `@dnd-kit/core` — not `react-beautiful-dnd` (unmaintained).
- Optimistic update on drop: update local state immediately, then sync to Supabase. Revert on error.
- Card order stored as `position: float` (use midpoint algorithm to avoid reordering all cards).
- Keyboard drag-and-drop must work (accessibility requirement).

---

## 12. STYLING

- Tailwind CSS utility classes only. No CSS modules, no styled-components.
- Design tokens defined in `tailwind.config.ts` — no hardcoded hex values in JSX.
- Dark mode supported via `class` strategy (`dark:` prefix).
- No inline `style={{}}` except for dynamic values (e.g., drag preview position).

---

## 13. ERROR HANDLING

- Every async operation wrapped in try/catch. No unhandled promise rejections.
- User-facing errors shown via a toast system (`useToast` hook) — not console.log, not alerts.
- AI errors (rate limit, timeout) show a retry button, not a broken UI.
- Network errors distinguished from auth errors from server errors — different messages.

---

## 14. PERFORMANCE

- Virtualize long task lists (>50 cards per column) with `@tanstack/virtual`.
- Code-split by route. Payment and AI chat lazy-loaded.
- Supabase queries always scoped (never `select('*')` without a `where` in production).
- Images optimized: avatars served via Supabase Storage with size transforms.

---

## 15. SECURITY

- Never expose service role key on the frontend. Only anon key.
- Sanitize all user input before sending to AI (strip prompt injection attempts).
- Board invite links expire — generate via edge function, not frontend.
- Validate Telegram webhook origin on the backend, not frontend.

---

## 16. TESTING

- Unit test: pure utility functions in `src/lib/utils.ts` and prompt builders.
- Integration test: custom hooks with `@testing-library/react-hooks` + Supabase mock.
- E2E test (Playwright): critical flows only — auth, create board, AI task breakdown, payment.
- No snapshot tests.

---

## 17. DO NOT

- Do not call Supabase directly in JSX or event handlers.
- Do not store sensitive data (tokens, keys) in state or localStorage.
- Do not use `useEffect` to sync state — derive it or use React Query.
- Do not auto-assign AI tasks without user confirmation.
- Do not block the UI while waiting for AI — always stream or show skeleton.
- Do not hardcode user IDs, board IDs, or plan limits.
